ogy.processors()\n   - Calls node.init(processorContext, processingExceptionHandler) on each node\n   - Initializes processor-specific state and resources\n\n10. **State Store Initialization** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StreamTask.java:262-278)\n    - StateManagerUtil.registerStateStores() registers state stores with ProcessorStateManager\n    - Loads state from disk or creates fresh stores\n    - Initializes changelog topic recovery if needed\n\n### Key Data Structures\n\n- **ProcessorTopology** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorTopology.java)\n  - Immutable representation of the compiled topology\n  - Contains lists of ProcessorNode, SourceNode, SinkNode, and StateStore objects\n  - Maintains mappings between stores and changelog topics\n\n- **InternalTopologyBuilder** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java)\n  - Stateful builder maintaining node factories and state factories\n  - Performs topology validation and optimization\n  - Maps stores to changelog topics and manages copartitioning constraints\n\n- **StreamTask** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StreamTask.java)\n  - Executes a ProcessorTopology for a specific set of input partitions\n  - Manages processor context and state management\n  - Coordinates record processing and punctuation scheduling\n\nThis architecture separates concerns: StreamsBuilder provides DSL abstractions, InternalStreamsBuilder optimizes the graph, InternalTopologyBuilder compiles to a physical topology, and StreamTask executes it with proper state and context management."
